value.title: Sir David Attenborough on Joe Biden, Christmas wrapping... and flamingos
value.excerpt: Like many of us, Sir David Attenborough has had to adapt to new ways of working since the coronavirus pandemic took hold this spring. For his latest series, the 93-year-old - who has been shielding - had to record some of his voiceovers from his home in south-west London.

value.title: Jeff Stein: Trump's last-minute push for larger stimulus checks example of 'long-running tension' with other Republicans
value.excerpt: In an interview on Hill.TV’s “Rising,” Stein said Trump had told allies that he wanted new stimulus checks as large as $2,000 per person, even as congressional leadership is preparing a package that would provide checks of just $600 each.

value.title: Why Charlie Baker isn’t planning to get a public vaccination like Mike Pence
value.excerpt: The Massachusetts governor wants to wait until he qualifies — and isn't sure elected officials are the most effective officials to inspire public confidence.

value.title: Covid-19 Live Updates: Pence, McConnell and Other U.S. Officials Receive Vaccines
value.excerpt: Experts fear the country’s deep partisan divide may limit the vaccine's reach to Republicans. France’s president details his symptoms.

value.title: Bidens to receive first dose of Pfizer vaccine Monday
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden and incoming first lady Jill Biden will receive the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine on Monday in Delaware, transition spokesperson Jen Psaki told reporters on a briefing call Friday.

value.title: Trump appoints 1776 Commission members in last-minute bid to advance 'patriotic education'
value.excerpt: The group will be led by the president of the conservative Hillsdale College, Larry Arnn, a longtime Trump ally, the White House said.

value.title: Trump, ahead of FDA, says Moderna's COVID-19 vaccine has been approved
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump in a tweet on Friday said Moderna Inc's vaccine had been approved and would ship immediately, although the U.S. Food and Drug Administration has made no public announcement yet regarding its decision.

value.title: Trump, targeting McConnell and top Republicans, urges them to 'get tougher' in election fight
value.excerpt: President Trump is again taking aim at Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell after the top Republican and Trump ally earlier this week recognized President-elect Joe Biden's White House victory.

value.title: Biden transition head speaks out on 'difficult and intense' process
value.excerpt: Biden’s longtime chief of staff and a former senator, says that leading Biden’s transition team “has been the most difficult and intense workload that I've ever experienced.” "I thought we [saw] the most difficult transition because of the Great Recession,

value.title: ‘He called me kiddo’: Jill Biden says WSJ essay was ‘such a surprise’
value.excerpt: "One of the things I'm most proud of is my doctorate," incoming First Lady Jill Biden told Stephen Colbert while responding to the WSJ's controversial op-ed.

value.title: Trump praises Tuberville after Alabama GOP senator-elect leaves open objecting to election results January 6
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump lauded Tommy Tuberville this week after the Republican Alabama senator-elect said he is not ruling out joining a House member to object to the election results when Congress meets in a joint session to accept the votes of the Electoral College.

value.title: Supreme Court throws out challenge to Trump's plan to exclude undocumented immigrants from census count
value.excerpt: The Supreme Court on Friday threw out a challenge to President Donald Trump's bid to exclude undocumented immigrants from being counted when seats in Congress are divvied up between the states next year.

value.title: Atlantic City auctions off chance to push demolish button on former Trump casino
value.excerpt: The implosion of one of President Donald Trump's former Atlantic City casinos is being delayed by a few weeks.

value.title: Pence gets COVID-19 vaccine to show it's 'safe and effective'
value.excerpt: Calling it a “medical miracle,” Vice President Mike Pence on Friday morning publicly took the new coronavirus vaccine. value.title: Kamala Harris prepares for her historic vice presidency by studying Joe Biden's legacy
value.excerpt: As Kamala Harris prepares for the vice presidency, she is learning from a person who knows more about the job than almost anyone in the world: President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: Trump says Moderna COVID-19 vaccine distribution will start 'immediately,' signals to Europe vaccines to come
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday said distribution of the Moderna vaccine will start "immediately" after it was "overwhelmingly approved" this week, while signaling to European nations that have been "hit hard" that coronavirus vaccines would be "on their way" to them, as well.

value.title: Jill Biden says her doctorate is among her proudest achievements: 'I worked so hard for it'
value.excerpt: Jill Biden was surprised by a recent newspaper op-ed piece suggesting she stop using the "Dr." title before her name, she told TV host Stephen Colbert on Thursday evening.

value.title: Trump has discussed rebooting 'The Apprentice' as he prepares to leave the White House, according to a report
value.excerpt: The president has reportedly talked to aides about the prospect of reviving the reality TV show in which he starred.

value.title: Covid: US Vice-President Mike Pence to receive vaccine
value.excerpt: President Mike Pence is to receive the coronavirus vaccine live on television at later on Friday. The White House said the aim of the move was to "promote the safety and efficacy of the vaccine and build confidence among the American people".

value.title: Late Night Compares Trump Health Adviser, Paul Alexander, to a Comic Book Villain
value.excerpt: The former Health and Human Services adviser’s leaked emails encouraged herd immunity to deal with the pandemic, writing of Americans, “We want them infected.”

value.title: Joe Biden Wears a ‘Kick Me’ Sign
value.excerpt: Critics like AOC and Sanders believe there is no price to be paid, and benefits to be gained, by publicly pressuring the new administration.

value.title: 'Accept defeat': See Trump ally's message after election loss
value.excerpt: Former New Jersey Governor Chris Christie talks to CNN's Chris Cuomo about the election and how President Donald Trump and some Republicans have refused to concede.

value.title: Virginia gubernatorial candidate says ‘Trump should declare martial law’
value.excerpt: Virginia Republican state Sen. Amanda Chase, an outspoken Trump supporter, former small business owner and gubernatorial hopeful, doubled down on disputed voter fraud claims and said Thursday that her state needs an election audit – through martial law, if necessary.

value.title: Omar says her father died of coronavirus because of Trump's 'criminal neglect'
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar said Friday that her father died of Covid-19 in June because of “criminal neglect” by the Trump administration.
